<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Leishman</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-12-16"><hi rend="italic">December 16,
                                    1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Hay informs Mr. Leishman that Admiral Cotton has been instructed to
                            convey Consul Davis to Alexandretta when he desires to go. Regrets
                            demanded should be explicit, but not humiliating, and apology by the
                            governor and the punishment of the offending police may be accepted as
                            sufficient.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>